defaultAn organization’s success and 
defaultcompetitiveness depends on its ability to embrace diversity
defaultand draw on the skills, understanding and experience of its people. The potential rewards of
defaultdiversity are significant: recruiting staff from the widest possible pool will unlock talent and
defaultmake a
default major contribution to the impact of research and will benefit the economic and social
defaultwellbeing of the UK. RCUK expects that equality and diversity therefore is embedded at all
defaultlevels and in all aspects of normal research practice.
default&#xa0;
defaultRCUK expect those in r
defaulteceipt of Research Council funding to:
default&#xa0;
